social_posts.post_text: I know I’m HELLA LATE but she didn’t have access to her phone for the past 7 days (spiritual retreat). I wanna Congratulate my Vegas sister @iamanetra for making @rupaulsdragrace Season 15 I met @iamanetra before she started Drag and she has always been a genuine humble spirit! The drive this kid has is insane! Her growth, determination, and dedication to Drag is the best I’ve seen in the game! I know these girls are fierce but Baby y’all better watch out because I know my sister SLAYS! I’m so proud of you and so happy you’re following your dreams! Help me end the Year with a bang! Catch me as I perform all week long in Rupaul’s Drag Race Live, here at The Flamingo in Las Vegas! 2022 has been such a transformative year! Let’s just say I put down the foundation and planted the seeds to blossom, not only in my Career but she’s spiritually elevating as well! So excited to close this year doing what I love! Thank you to everyone who supports this art form 

Hair by @gowigorgohome

To some you’re a Devil, others you’re a saving grace. To me Eshu is my everything! The one who fully understands me and never turns his back. Orishas are the very essence of Nature. They are our deified ancestors who have ascended so that they might help us in our lives. I’ve made a lot of changes this year but the biggest one was going through my initiation into Lucumi. I’ve faced a lot of challenges along the way within myself, but the biggest reward is feeling liberated and connected to a higher power that has been there all along but now I’m connected and guided by it’s loving embrace. I recognize a lot of people won’t understand my beliefs and that’s ok. I believe life is all about evolution, and instead of me trying to explain why this makes since for you I want my character and my way of living to be all the proof that’s needed.

Happy birthday Ramón Hardiman! You are hands down one of the most realist and loving persons I know! Best friends for over 15 years and we’ve seen the world together! We continue to push each other to be our best versions, chasing our dreams together, and supporting each other through the high and the lows. I’m so thankful to have you in my life!  Thank you for supporting me from being homeless, to making Drag Race, to even my spiritual journey!  You always saw the best in me. For that I will always be your biggest supporter and have your back through whatever life throws at us. My love for you simply can’t be measured! May this day be filled with blessings!

I’m so happy that after years of putting in that work my baby @iamanetra is getting all the love and recognition she deserves! You stay keeping your  energy high vibes and watch the blessings keep coming through nonstop! #teamanetra #rupaulsdragrace #rpdr

3 months ago I decided to make the biggest change in my life. I made Ocha and Crowned  Orisha Elegua. Thanks to my God Father @xuanito702 and Obatala I have found my true destiny and purpose in this life. Although it’s only been 3 months my life has drastically changed. I have such a greater understanding of who I am and with that came real self love, true peace, and motivation to give 💯 in everything I do. The amount of blessings Orisha has given me is beyond anything I’ve ever experienced. That’s why I was so honored to play Aña for the King who birthed me Owner of all heads Obatala. Padrino I pray Obatala give you many blessings, true joy, and prosperity! My love for you simply cannot be measured! Oku Odun @xuanito702 #Aña #santo #obatala #lukumi #happybirthday

Last year I went to the River and cried out my heart to Oshun. I was feeling stagnant, unseen, and unworthy. I prayed if she’d give me a chance to be on TV again to show how much I’ve grown that I would give my all in everything I do. This woman has answered my prayers 10x over. Oshun’s love saved my life, rejuvenated me, gave me a reason worth living!  The confidence you guys see was gifted to me by my mother, she has shown me I have everything I need within. Win or lose she always treats me as her divine child. I will forever sing her praises because I’ve never felt a love like I do with Oshun. I’m proud to be a Santero. I have been the absolute best version of myself since my initiation and crowning my head Orisha Elegua. It is however my mother Oshun who has led me to this beautiful religion and has taught me how to love unconditionally looking beyond physicality. I decided to dedicate my Finale to the woman who I believe helped me get there in the first place. MEFEREFUN OSHUN 🍯 💛🌻 Also please help me tag @beyonce and her team @parkwood because with her visuals of the gift I was able to let my fears go of joining African spirituality. I just want her to see that her album really did change lives including mines!

I never could’ve imagined I would leave such an impact from being on Allstars 8! I’m just so beyond thankful to experience this and do what I do best & that’s PERFORM!
